The shoe’s rugged Pro Grip outsole is made of a special rubber compound offering superior grip on every terrain and surface. The Ridge Trail AQM for women is equipped with a Cushion Fit midsole that reliably absorbs shock while being extremely lightweight and offering a maximum of comfort. PRO TOUCH’s extremely easy-to-use Quick Lace System provides an evenly distributed pressure around the entire foot, resulting in a significantly enhanced tight and comfortable fit. To protect you against bad weather, the Ridge Trail features an upper made of light canvas, mesh, and synthetics with an integrated waterproof, windproof, and breathable Aquamax® membrane. column13: Sequence AQX W, McKinely, Active Outdoor

column3: The Sequence AQX is a waterproof, well cushioned, and lightweight\
outdoor boot designed to offer maximum performance,\
comfort, and breathability. Although it is made of the lightest\
materials available, it offers enough support for serious trekking\
and hiking. The anatomical shape of the collar enhances the freedom\
of movement while supporting and protecting the Achilles\
area. The overall construction of the boot is based on McKINLEY’s\
new Butterfly footwear technology, featuring the new Butterfly\
Shank and the Butterfly Lacing Support. The Butterfly Shank is a\
thermoplastic urethane link in the outsole between the heel and\
the forefoot that allows a smooth and stable impact when the foot\
hits the ground. It also provides torsional stability and strength\
to the midfoot, thus supporting an easy toe-off. The new Butterfly\
Lacing Support is a „wrap-around“ lacing design that links the\
classic metal-hook lacing to the boot’s upper for a more individual\
adjustment. In addition to the Butterfly Technology features, the\
Sequence AQX is equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX\
® technology, making this extremely versatile lightweight\
boot super reliable in all conditions.\

column13: Ewa Softshell Jacket ux, Mountain tec, McKinley

column2:
When the conditions get really cold and wet, the Ewa jacket is the one piece of equipment you definitely want to bring along. Nothing beats the price/performance ratio of this comfortable and highly protective three-layer softshell. Equipped with DRY PLUS wind and the Airflow ventilation system, the robust fabric of the Ewa softshell will serve you as the literal shield to protect you from the elements. The construction of the fabric offers a mechanical stretch that offers great freedom of movement. In addition to being windproof, the jacket is also highly breathable, guaranteeing that your body climate is well regulated even if you are hot and perspiring. Opening or closing the front pockets individually adjusts the airflow of the ventilation system. To make sure that your valuables are not lost when you aerate while in motion, there are safety pockets inside the front pockets.

\

\

No matter what’s your activity and how hot it is outside, these pants will provide a maximum of body temperature management and won’t inhibit your freedom of movement, even when you are climbing or running. An unnoticeable internal waist adjustment system guarantees best individual fit and comfort. Two open front pockets and  one zipped safety front pocket offer plenty of space for small items.

column2:

This very lightweight running shoe is designed for young neutral-gait runners who need a shoe that provides a pleasurable, well-cushioned, and low-impact ride. The OZ Pro Jr features a pre-moulded I-Shape insole for stability and fit. The Cushion Fit midsole construction is designed to reliably absorb shock and provide high comfort at an extremely reduced weight. An abrasion-resistant Easy Grip outsole offers reliable traction.

\

column13: Road Running Shoe OZ Pro Men

column2:
Great comfort and low weight: The OZ Pro for men is a well-cushioned running shoe for neutral-gait runners who are looking for lightweight footwear for longer distances. The design of the shoe is sleek and reduced, but it’s not compromising any of its important performance properties: It features Cushion Fit, which is a midsole construction designed to absorb shock and provide high comfort at a very low weight. The Easy Grip outsole is very abrasion-resistant and offers good and reliable grip. On the inside, a breathable OrthoLite® insole ensures great fit as well as perfect moisture management and an odourless and bacteria-free foot climate. 

\

column13: Trail Running Shoe Ridge Trail AQM Men

column2:
PRO TOUCH’s top trail running shoe Ridge Trail AQM for men is fully equipped and designed for serious trail action. The rough Pro Grip outsole is made of a special rubber compound offering superior grip on every terrain and surface. The Ridge Trail AQM was also designed to offer a maximum of comfort, which is realized by integrating a Cushion Fit midsole that reliably absorbs shock while being extremely lightweight. PRO TOUCH’s Quick Lace System provides an evenly distributed pressure around the entire foot, resulting in a significantly improved tight and comfortable fit. Since you should always be prepared for any kind of weather, the Ridge Trail features an upper made of light canvas, mesh, and synthetics with an integrated waterproof, windproof, and breathable Aquamax® membrane. This technology does not only keep the rain out, it also regulates the foot climate and keeps you comfortable and dry inside your shoes at all times. Last, but not least, a well cushioned and pre-moulded OrthoLite® insole guarantees additional breathability and avoids odours and bacteria that may develop around the foot during long and intense runs.

\

column13: Road Running Shoe Tokyo Stability II Men

column2:
With the Tokyo Stability II for men, PRO TOUCH offers a stable and solid running shoe with great comfort and flex. The breathable shoe is designed for runners with a normal arch, providing a comfortable ride mile after. The Speed Rebel is a high-performance indoor handball shoe that combines minimum weight with excellent comfort and support. To stabilize the foot during extreme lateral movements and quick directional changes, the Speed Rebel is equipped with Stability Wings. In addition the Pro Wrap technology  further re-enforces the shoe and gives the foot for enhanced motion control and stability. The upper consists of tough PU and a lightweight technical mesh to ensure high breathability  and comfort. The pre-shaped OrthoLite® insole is highly breathable, long lasting and anti-microbial. In combination with the lightweight midsole compound, it provides superior cushioning and durability. The ProBridge is a lightweight arch support that provides additional torsional rigidity in the midfoot while retaining the structural integrity of the shoe. The non-marking Pro Grip outsole has premium grip characteristics and a high abrasion resistance.

In addition the Pro Wrap technology  further re-enforces the shoe and gives the foot for enhanced motion control and stability. The upper consists of tough PU and a lightweight technical mesh to ensure high breathability  and comfort. The pre-shaped OrthoLite® insole is highly breathable, long lasting and anti-microbial. In combination with the lightweight midsole compound, it provides superior cushioning and durability. The ProBridge is a lightweight arch support that provides additional torsional rigidity in the midfoot while retaining the structural integrity of the shoe. The non-marking Pro Grip outsole has premium grip characteristics and a high abrasion resistance.

The Rebel has been optimised for performance and comfort. A breathable lightweight upper mesh in conjunction with the PRO TOUCH Wrap technology provides the foot with enhanced motion control and fit. In addition the Rebel is equipped with anatomically shaped and pre-moulded EVA I-Shape insoles for improved comfort. The non-marking Dura Grip outsole offers good grip and reliable durability for a multitude of different indoor sports.

The upper consists of tough PU and a lightweight technical mesh to ensure high breathability  and comfort. The pre-shaped OrthoLite® insole is highly breathable, long lasting and anti-microbial. In combination with the lightweight midsole compound, it provides superior cushioning and durability. The ProBridge is a lightweight arch support that provides additional torsional rigidity in the midfoot while retaining the structural integrity of the shoe. The non-marking Pro Grip outsole has premium grip characteristics and a high abrasion resistance.

A ¾ running tight offers a great amount of support and compression while leaving the legs well ventilated on hot summer days. The fabric of the PRO TOUCH Iris tight for women is very elastic, breathable, and equipped with DRY PLUS moisture, a fibre technology that rapidly transports moisture away from the body to keep you dry and comfortable. Flatlock seams reduce the risk of chafing. A key pocket and a zipped pocket at the back offer plenty of space for small items. Strategically placed 360-degree reflective elements improve your safety when you run in low light conditions.

The Rebel Jr was specifically developed for young athletes looking for a lightweight, stable and comfortable performance shoe. A breathable lightweight upper mesh in conjunction with the PRO TOUCH Wrap technology provides the foot with enhanced motion control and fit. The Control Bridge midfoot support and a lightweight midsole compound enhance shock absorption and stability. In addition the Rebel is equipped with anatomically shaped and pre-moulded EVA I-Shape insoles for improved comfort. To protect the upper from excessive wear the toe area is re-enforced with an abrasion resistant PU material. The non-marking Dura Grip outsole offers good grip and reliable durability for a multitude of different indoor sports.

The Speed Rebel is a high-performance indoor handball shoe that combines minimum weight with excellent comfort and support. To stabilize the foot during extreme lateral movements and quick directional changes, the Speed Rebel is equipped with Stability Wings. In addition the Pro Wrap technology  further re-enforces the shoe and gives the foot for enhanced motion control and stability. The upper consists of tough PU and a lightweight technical mesh to ensure high breathability  and comfort. The pre-shaped OrthoLite® insole is highly breathable, long lasting and anti-microbial. In combination with the lightweight midsole compound, it provides superior cushioning and durability. The ProBridge is a lightweight arch support that provides additional torsional rigidity in the midfoot while retaining the structural integrity of the shoe. The non-marking Pro Grip outsole has premium grip characteristics and a high abrasion resistance.

column13: Road Running Shoe Chicago Stability II Women

column2:
The women’s version of the Chicago Stability running shoe was adapted to women’s specific needs. It’s a comfortable and breathable running shoe for beginners to intermediate runners, offering plenty of guidance for a neutral gait. The shoe features an anatomically shaped and pre-moulded I-Shape insole for superior stability and fit. The Cushion Fit midsole construction of the Chicago Stability is designed to reliably absorb shock and provide high comfort. The weight of the Cushion Fit midsole is reduced to the minimum, without compromising its durability. Whilst reducing the overall weight of the shoe, the stability was improved by integrating a Control Bridge moulded arch support around the midfoot area. The advanced Dura Grip outsole material provides enhanced grip and added durability for road running.

\

Available in colors: White/grey/light blue and pruple/violet/white

\

Great comfort and low weight: The OZ Pro for men is a well-cushioned running shoe for neutral-gait runners who are looking for lightweight footwear for longer distances. The design of the shoe is sleek and reduced, but it’s not compromising any of its important performance properties: It features Cushion Fit, which is a midsole construction designed to absorb shock and provide high comfort at a very low weight. The Easy Grip outsole is very abrasion-resistant and offers good and reliable grip. On the inside, a breathable OrthoLite® insole ensures great fit as well as perfect moisture management and an odourless and bacteria-free foot climate.

\

Available in colors: Black/white/red, blue/green/white, blue/orange/black and white/black/blue

\

The new OZ Pro for women may look reduced, sleek and modern, but it is one of PRO TOUCH’s best-cushioned running shoes for neutral-gait runners. The shoe features Cushion Fit, which is a midsole construction designed to reliably absorb shock and provide high comfort at a very low weight. Many other components of the shoe like the upper and parts of the sole construction were also redesigned to be lighter than in any other PRO TOUCH running shoe. The Easy Grip outsole is very abrasion-resistant and offers good and reliable grip. On the inside of the OZ Pro W, a breathable OrthoLite® insole ensures great fit as well as perfect moisture management and an odourless and bacteria-free foot climate. 

\

Available in colors: Blue/dark pink/white, Purple/light violet/white and balck/pink

\

column13: Road Running Shoe RUNlight New York Men

column2:
This lightweight men’s running shoe is designed for serious, underpronating to neutral runners who work out or compete on a regular basis, preferably on hard surfaces like tarmac, gravel, or solid soil. For a sock-like fit and maximum comfort, the New York from PRO TOUCH’s RUNlight collection is made of the lightest, yet durable performance materials available. This starts with a synthetic mesh/PU mix of the upper construction, which delivers an incredible light feeling. At the same time the material is soft, breathable, and still stable enough to provide enough foothold around the ankle for a safe run. The low-weight internal Pro Bridge delivers the energy from impact to toe-off to allow a smooth and efficient running style. For a dry feeling under the foot, the anatomically shaped and pre-moulded OrthoLite® insole is breathable, moisture wicking, and anti-microbial. In combination with the lightweight Pro Cushion midsole construction with focus on rear and forefoot cushioning, this lightweight midsole provides superior shock absorption and durability at minimal weight. A non-marking Dura Grip rubber outsole adds cushioning and reliable friction without adding one unnecessary gram to the construction.

\

Available in color: Blue/orange and white/blue

\

In addition the Rebel is equipped with anatomically shaped and pre-moulded EVA I-Shape insoles for improved comfort. To protect the upper from excessive wear the toe area is re-enforced with an abrasion resistant PU material. The non-marking Dura Grip outsole offers good grip and reliable durability for a multitude of different indoor sports.

The Speed Rebel is a high-performance indoor handball shoe that combines minimum weight with excellent comfort and support. To stabilize the foot during extreme lateral movements and quick directional changes, the Speed Rebel is equipped with Stability Wings. In addition the Pro Wrap technology  further re-enforces the shoe and gives the foot for enhanced motion control and stability. The upper consists of tough PU and a lightweight technical mesh to ensure high breathability  and comfort. The pre-shaped OrthoLite® insole is highly breathable, long lasting and anti-microbial. In combination with the lightweight midsole compound, it provides superior cushioning and durability. The ProBridge is a lightweight arch support that provides additional torsional rigidity in the midfoot while retaining the structural integrity of the shoe. The non-marking Pro Grip outsole has premium grip characteristics and a high abrasion resistance.

The Control Bridge midfoot support and a lightweight midsole compound enhance shock absorption and stability. In addition the Rebel is equipped with anatomically shaped and pre-moulded EVA I-Shape insoles for improved comfort. To protect the upper from excessive wear the toe area is re-enforced with an abrasion resistant PU material. The non-marking Dura Grip outsole offers good grip and reliable durability for a multitude of different indoor sports.  

\

The Speed Rebel is a high-performance indoor handball shoe that combines minimum weight with excellent comfort and support. To stabilize the foot during extreme lateral movements and quick directional changes, the Speed Rebel is equipped with Stability Wings. In addition the Pro Wrap technology  further re-enforces the shoe and gives the foot for enhanced motion control and stability. The upper consists of tough PU and a lightweight technical mesh to ensure high breathability  and comfort. The pre-shaped OrthoLite® insole is highly breathable, long lasting and anti-microbial. In combination with the lightweight midsole compound, it provides superior cushioning and durability. The ProBridge is a lightweight arch support that provides additional torsional rigidity in the midfoot while retaining the structural integrity of the shoe. The non-marking Pro Grip outsole has premium grip characteristics and a high abrasion resistance.

The Control Bridge midfoot support and a lightweight midsole compound enhance shock absorption and stability. In addition the Rebel is equipped with anatomically shaped and pre-moulded EVA I-Shape insoles for improved comfort. To protect the upper from excessive wear the toe area is re-enforced with an abrasion resistant PU material. The non-marking Dura Grip outsole offers good grip and reliable durability for a multitude of different indoor sports.  

\

The Speed Rebel is a high-performance indoor handball shoe that combines minimum weight with excellent comfort and support. To stabilize the foot during extreme lateral movements and quick directional changes, the Speed Rebel is equipped with Stability Wings. In addition the Pro Wrap technology  further re-enforces the shoe and gives the foot for enhanced motion control and stability. The upper consists of tough PU and a lightweight technical mesh to ensure high breathability  and comfort. The pre-shaped OrthoLite® insole is highly breathable, long lasting and anti-microbial. In combination with the lightweight midsole compound, it provides superior cushioning and durability. The ProBridge is a lightweight arch support that provides additional torsional rigidity in the midfoot while retaining the structural integrity of the shoe. The non-marking Pro Grip outsole has premium grip characteristics and a high abrasion resistance.

column2:

\

column13: McKINLEY pop up tent active outdoor camping koala 240

column2:

\

column13: McKINLEY family tent active outdoor camping Samos 6

column2:
The largest McKinley family tent with two opposite sleeping cabins. This spacious tent is perfect for longer camping holidays.

\

Outer tent: polyester, main seams tape-sealed, 3,000mm water column;

\

column13: McKINLEY active outdoor camping tent nevada 3

column2:
Three-person tent with a slightly higher dome for additional comfort. The Nevada 3 is well ventilated, has a robust PE floor and offers easy pitching thanks to the intuitive colour coding instructions. Store and carry it in the included oversized carrying bag.

\

column13: McKINLEY family tent active outdoor alpha 5

column2:
Classic family tent for weekends and camping holidays. Due to the two adjacent sleeping cabins, the awning offers a spacious interior.

\

Outer tent: 185T polyester, PU coated, tape-sealed seams, 3,000mm water column;

\

Inner tent: polyester; floor: polyester 10,000mm water column;

\

column13: McKINLEY active outdoor camping tent Kea 3

column2:
At less than 1kg per person, the Kea 3 is a lightweight tent for a variety of occasions. Whether you go trekking, hiking or simply camping, it offers reliable rain protection and great ventilation thanks to the large adjustable vent under the roof and the mesh door.

\

column13: McKINLEY family tent active outdoor camping alpha 4

column2:
Classic family tent for weekends and camping holidays. Due to the two adjacent sleeping cabins, the awning offers a spacious interior.

\

Outer tent: 185T polyester, PU coated, tape-sealed seams, 3,000mm water column;

\

Inner tent: polyester; floor: polyester 10,000mm water column;

\

Top-quality and extremely well equipped tunnel tent designed for extended trips. The tunnel shape offers plenty of storage space at a very low weight. Reflective rope tighteners eliminate tripping hazards in the dark.

\

The Bali is a great beach accessory, providing either protection from the wind or the sun, or creating some privacy when you want it. The Bali’s large zip opening serves as an additional floor sheet when opened. Easy colour coding set-up.

\

As its name implies, this tent is a compact 2-person tent with a total weight of only 1.9kg, complete with a small compression bag ideal for trekking. The Compactlight 2 is waterproof. Adjustable webbing straps give additional stability to the structure and guarantee that the rainfly is fully covering the tent body.

\

column13: mckinley active outdoor hiking rucksacks cougar 40

column2:
Depending on the size, our top hiking backpack comes as a daypack or as a backpack for multiple-day hikes. The ventilated back net ensures excellent breathability and the pack can be adjusted ideally to the torso length with the adjustable straps. The new Ergovent Vario back panel transforms the Cougar into a body-contact backpack in no time. Features: Ergovent Vario back system, rain cover, integrated side pockets, hiking pole fixation. Material: Nylon 210D Double Diamond Ripstop / Nylon 210D Stripe Twill.

\

The 1-kg/1-person tent has an incredibly small packing size and is ideal for bike or motorcycle tours. With its aluminium pole structure, it remains very stable in high winds.

\

Outer tent: polyester, PU coated, 3,000mm water column;

\

column13: McKINLEY active outdoor camping tent kreta 5

column2:
The Kreta 5 is McKINLEY’s robust and extra large tunnel tent for one entire family. This tent offers adult standing height throughout (max. 1.90cm) and enough room for five people. The Kreta 5 consists of three basic parts: two bedrooms (one for three and one for two persons) and a large living chamber with three windows and a side doors, all with mesh for mosquito-free ventilation and integrated PE floor. The third part is a small wind-protected outside porch with an additional tent entrance. The DualFlow ventilation system provides great air exchange through all parts of the Kreta 5. The colour coding helps with the pitching of the tent, which comes complete with an oversized carrying bag.

\

If you are looking for extra stability and protection, the McKINLEY Escape series offers fully waterproof tunnel tents for trekking, hiking or camping with robust 8.5mm aluminium poles and a total of 20 strong aluminium pegs. The adjustable webbing system gives additional stability. The Escape 4 is designed for four people, sharing the enormous total floor space of 2.30m x 4.35m, including the sleeping chamber and a separate, spacious vestibule. A large ventilation pocket makes sure that the entire tent is well ventilated if desired.

\

column13: McKINLEY active outdoor camping tent matuka 4

column2:
With extra width and extra length, this tent is the largest of our Matuka family and sleeps up to four adults. Sturdy 9.5mm poles support the additional size. Apart from that, the Matuka 4 offers all the known Matuka features like the additional floor for the vestibule, large windows, a mesh door for efficient ventilation, and an oversized carrying bag.

\

column13: McKINLEY active outdoor  camping tent Kos 4

column2:
Large enough for four people to sleep and plenty of additional space to serve as your holiday living or dining room: the Kos 4 is one of our most spacious outdoor camping tents, with two separate sleeping compartments and a large vestibule with mesh windows, multiple side gear lofts, and a full, integrated PE floor. Once taken out of its oversized carrying bag, the Kos 4 is quickly pitched thanks to the easy colour coding. The poles of the Kos 4 are made of extra strong fibreglass. 

\

If you are looking for extra stability and protection, the McKINLEY Escape series offers fully waterproof tunnel tents for trekking, hiking or camping with robust 8.5mm aluminium poles and a total of 20 strong aluminium pegs. The adjustable webbing system gives additional stability. The Escape 3 has enough space for three people. In addition to the separate sleeping chamber, the tent offers a spacious vestibule. A large ventilation pocket makes sure that the entire tent is well ventilated if desired.

\

The Blackfoot bags can be connected to a second bag to create a large two-person bag.

column13: mountain tec softshell jacket gawa men

column2:
Softshell jackets are no longer inferior to hardshells when it comes to full weather protection: The new Gawa softshell will protect you from the elements and help you perform at your best, no matter whether your favourite activity is climbing, trekking, hiking, ski touring, or snowshoeing. This 3-layer softshell offers the same performance level that you would expect from a hardshell, at the same time it’s softer and lighter. It battles the elements and keeps you dry and comfortable with our premium AQUAMAX® 20.20 membrane, which is waterproof and breathable, Airflow ventilation, fully taped seams, a detachable snowskirt, waterproof zips, and a detachable hood. The stretch fabric and pre-formed elbows for great freedom of movement, a brushed tricot application in the neck area, an adjustable jacket bottom, and a chin guard guarantee optimum fit and comfort. column13: Lanila Padded Jacket ux, Mountain tec, McKinley

column2:
If you need extra warmth on your trekking expedition or hiking trip without a bulky feel and excessive weight, the Lanila padded jacket with PrimaLoft® insulation is probably one of the most functional jackets you can bring. The Lanila can be worn as an insulating mid layer or as an outer layer. A durable water repellent finish makes sure that you don’t get soaked. And even if the PrimaLoft® padding should ever get moist or wet, it won’t loose any of its insulating properties. In addition, the PrimaLoft® fibres are inside a wind-breaking, high-density Polyamide fabric that blocks the wind to keep you warm. Two front pockets and one external chest pocket offer plenty of space for all your valuables, and the elastic binding cuffs guarantee a comfortable and tight fit. The entire jacket, including its storm hood, packs into its own internal pocket, so you can always bring it along.

\

Features: storm hood, chin guard, hood adjustment system, hem adjustment system, pre-formed elbows, YKK zippers

column13: Albany men, Mountain Tec, McKinley, Pants, Men

column3: Quick-drying and very versatile pants for a variety of\
mountain activities. Thanks to the 3XDRY® technology\
by schoeller®, the Albany pants are water and stain\
repellent on the outside as well as water absorbent on\
the inside. The technology keeps you dry and your body\
is cooled when perspiring, enhancing your performance.\
Pre-formed knees, an integrated belt, a partial\
elastic waist and the full stretch material guarantee\
perfect fit. With adjustable leg bottoms, you can wear\
the Albany with low-cut shoes as well as with hiking\
boots. Kevlar reinforcements on the lower leg protect\
the pants against abrasion caused by rocks. Available in\
both women’s and men’s styles, cuts and sizes.\

column13: McKINLEY active outdoor camping tent nevada 3

column3: Three-person tent with a slightly higher\
dome for additional comfort. The\
Nevada 3 is well ventilated, has a robust\
PE floor and offers easy pitching thanks\
to the intuitive colour coding instructions.\
For extra durability and protection,\
the tent is equipped with reinforcement\
patches on all potential\
stress points and a fully seam-sealed\
flysheet. For storage and transport, it\
comes complete with an oversized carrying\
bag. On the inside, a lamp holder\
adds to the overall comfort; on the outside,\
fluorescent guylines provide extra\
safety around the tent at night.\

column13: Coddy men long, McKinley, Active Outdoor

column3: The Coddy pants are our top functional Active Outdoor\
trekking pants, equipped with DRY PLUS and UV protection.\
With its many useful features, it is an essential\
part of your equipment: DRY PLUS and Polygiene® take\
care of your microclimate and keep you dry and free of\
odour-causing bacteria and fungi; with the bottom leg\
zippers, you can comfortably wear light low-cut outdoor\
shoes as well as hiking boots; the pre-formed knees, the\
partially elastic waist and the integrated belt ensure\
perfect fit. Last but not least: The zip-off function converts\
the Coddy into functional outdoor shorts for hot\
summer days. Great garment for travelling. Also available\
in special sizes for longer or shorter legs.\
\
Material: 100% Nylon\
\
Features: pre-formed knees, partial elastic waist,\
bottom-zip opening, integrated belt, zip-off pants\
\
Technology: DRY PLUS moisture, sun protection UPF 50,\
Polygiene®\

column13: Basalt AQX M, McKinley, Mountain Tec

column3: McKINLEY’s Basalt AQX is a great mid-cut trekking boot ideal\
for a multitude of outdoor activities. It resembles the perfect\
combination of weight, stability, weather protection and allterrain\
capability. The comfortable boot is equipped with\
waterproof and breathable AQUAMAX® technology to keep\
the feet dry and well conditioned at any time. The mid-cut\
design is perfect for the right amount of stability and protection\
around the ankles, yet not restricting the flexibility of\
the foot for quick and nimble hiking. The reliable McKINLEY\
Trekking outsole offers great grip and stability in any terrain.\
For additional comfort and stability, the Basalt features\
protectors on both heels and toe. The lacing with Butterfly\
Lacing Support and additional deep pull hook provides perfect\
fit. The Basalt AQX is a true performer for any weather\
and outdoor adventure!\
Material: Suede Leather/Synthetic\
Liner: Synthetic\
Outsole: McKINLEY Trekking\
Midsole: PU/rubber\
Weight: 385g (size 42)\
Special: AQUAMAX® Elite, Confort Fit, Butterf ly Lacing\
Support, Deep Pull Hook, Metal hook, Easy Entrance\
Loop, Rubber Toe Protector, Heel Protector\

multi-functional hiking boot. To offer comfort, stability,\

Ortholite insoles (one of the leading insoles for comfort and\

– fully equipped and very affordable!\

column13: Sequence AQX W, McKinely, Active Outdoor

column3: The Sequence AQX is a waterproof, well cushioned, and lightweight\
outdoor boot designed to offer maximum performance,\
comfort, and breathability. Although it is made of the lightest\
materials available, it offers enough support for serious trekking\
and hiking. The anatomical shape of the collar enhances the freedom\
of movement while supporting and protecting the Achilles\
area. The overall construction of the boot is based on McKINLEY’s\
new Butterfly footwear technology, featuring the new Butterfly\
Shank and the Butterfly Lacing Support. The Butterfly Shank is a\
thermoplastic urethane link in the outsole between the heel and\
the forefoot that allows a smooth and stable impact when the foot\
hits the ground. It also provides torsional stability and strength\
to the midfoot, thus supporting an easy toe-off. The new Butterfly\
Lacing Support is a „wrap-around“ lacing design that links the\
classic metal-hook lacing to the boot’s upper for a more individual\
adjustment. In addition to the Butterfly Technology features, the\
Sequence AQX is equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX\
® technology, making this extremely versatile lightweight\
boot super reliable in all conditions.\
Material: Synthetic & Mesh\
Liner: Synthetic\
Outsole: Rubber (STICO 3)\
Midsole: molded EVA (high cut)\
Weight: 450 g\
Special: AQUAMAX®, Ortholite®, Performance Fit, Butterf ly\
Shank, Butterf ly Lacing Support, Deep Pull Hook, Metal\
Hook, Rubber Toe Protector, Comfort Cushion System\

column13: Magma AQX W, McKinley, Mountain Tec

column3: The Magma AQX is one of McKINLEY’s Active Outdoor trekking\
and hiking boots that is designed for maximum performance\
with minimum weight. It’s a great choice for outdoor\
enthusiasts looking for a versatile trekking boot at a highly\
competitive price. With an upper made of leather and synthetic,\
the Magma AQX is also equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof\
AQUAMAX® technology, making this all-rounder reliable\
in all conditions. In addition, the VIBRAM® outsole\
provides tremendous grip in any kind of weather and terrain.\
Its durable compound ensures extended life and extremely\
high friction on all surfaces. For ideal fit, the Magma AQX\
features a classic lacing system that runs through durable\
metal hooks with an additional deep pull hook and Butterfly\
support that links the lacing directly to the upper for a more\
individual adjustment.\
Material: Leather/Synthetic / Textile\
Liner: Synthetic\
Outsole: Vibram® (STICO 2)\
Midsole: PU\
Weight: 540 g\
Special: AQUAMAX®, Comfort Fit, Butterf ly Lacing\
Support, Deep Pull Hook, Metal Hook, Heel Protector,\
Rubber Toe Protector\

column13: Sequence AQX W, McKinely, Active Outdoor

column3: The Sequence AQX is a waterproof, well cushioned, and lightweight\
outdoor boot designed to offer maximum performance,\
comfort, and breathability. Although it is made of the lightest\
materials available, it offers enough support for serious trekking\
and hiking. The anatomical shape of the collar enhances the freedom\
of movement while supporting and protecting the Achilles\
area. The overall construction of the boot is based on McKINLEY’s\
new Butterfly footwear technology, featuring the new Butterfly\
Shank and the Butterfly Lacing Support. The Butterfly Shank is a\
thermoplastic urethane link in the outsole between the heel and\
the forefoot that allows a smooth and stable impact when the foot\
hits the ground. It also provides torsional stability and strength\
to the midfoot, thus supporting an easy toe-off. The new Butterfly\
Lacing Support is a „wrap-around“ lacing design that links the\
classic metal-hook lacing to the boot’s upper for a more individual\
adjustment. In addition to the Butterfly Technology features, the\
Sequence AQX is equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX\
® technology, making this extremely versatile lightweight\
boot super reliable in all conditions.\
Material: Synthetic & Mesh\
Liner: Synthetic\
Outsole: Rubber (STICO 3)\
Midsole: molded EVA (high cut)\
Weight: 450 g\
Special: AQUAMAX®, Ortholite®, Performance Fit, Butterf ly\
Shank, Butterf ly Lacing Support, Deep Pull Hook, Metal\
Hook, Rubber Toe Protector, Comfort Cushion System\

column13: Osorno AQX W, McKinley, X function

column3: The Osorno AQX W is a durable and waterproof trail shoe for\
active women who enjoy a good trail run or speed hike. This\
high-performance shoe is equipped with AQUAMAX® Elite, a\
reliable Vibram® outsole and a flexible and shock absorbing\
midsole for extra comfort and control. The mesh liner helps\
regulate the foot climate, the waterproof AQUAMAX® technology\
ensures additional breathability. The Fast Lace System\
of the Osorno AQX W easily allows you to re-adjust your\
shoes at any time; a protective flap covers the closure element\
of the system and the excess lace, avoiding them to get\
caught in branches and keeping dirt out.\

column13: mckinley mountain tec trekking shoes rimrock men

column2:
The Rimrock is a great choice for outdoor enthusiasts looking for a versatile trekking boot. The Rimrock II AQX is equipped with AQUAMAX® technology, making this all-rounder reliable in all conditions. In addition, the VIBRAM® outsole provides tremendous grip in any kind of weather. Its durable compound ensures extended life and extremely high friction on all surfaces. It is designed to expel unwanted stones very effectively on all terrains, which will make your hike safer and more comfortable. In addition, the Strobel construction guarantees extreme flexibility of the upper boot for great agility on the mountain.

\

column13: Killay Hardshell Jacket ux, Mountain tec, McKinley

column2:
The Killay hardshell is the perfect emergency jacket that you always want to carry when you are outside: It’s super lightweight, packs extremely small in a separate bag, has a storm hood, and comes with fully taped seams and McKINLEY’s high-performing waterproof and breathable AQUAMAX® 10.10 membrane. Whether it’s wind or water, the Killay will protect you from cooling down or getting soaked. To reduce the overall weight of the jacket and to provide a tight fit, the jacket has elastic hems that close tight around the wrists and the hip. It even has a chest pocket to fit its own compression bag or other small items. The Killay needs minimal space, so make sure to take it everywhere you go!

\

Features: storm hood, separate packing bag, waterproof zips, chin guard, fully taped seams, YKK zippers

\

column13: Cem Softshell Jacket wms, Mountain tec, McKinley

The stretchable fabric offers great comfort and ideal freedom of movement for most outdoor activities. The soft fabric has a pleasant, soft touch; in addition, it’s very breathable to allow the body climate to stay well balanced at all times. Two zipped front pockets offer plenty of space for small items.

\

Features: chin guard, hem adjustment system, adjustable cuffs

\

column13: Ewa Softshell Jacket ux, Mountain tec, McKinley

column2:
When the conditions get really cold and wet, the Ewa jacket is the one piece of equipment you definitely want to bring along. Nothing beats the price/performance ratio of this comfortable and highly protective three-layer softshell. Equipped with DRY PLUS wind and the Airflow ventilation system, the robust fabric of the Ewa softshell will serve you as the literal shield to protect you from the elements. The construction of the fabric offers a mechanical stretch that offers great freedom of movement. In addition to being windproof, the jacket is also highly breathable, guaranteeing that your body climate is well regulated even if you are hot and perspiring. To make sure that your valuables are not lost when you aerate while in motion, there are safety pockets inside the front pockets.

\

Features: zip-off hood, hood adjustment system, hem adjustment system, pre-formed elbows, ventilation, chin guard, adjustable cuffs

\

Technology: DRY PLUS wind, Airflow System, YKK zippers

column13: Emerson Hard Shell Rain Jacket ux

column2:
Lightweight and reliable hard shell for rainy days. Whether you wear your Emerson jacket in the mountains, travelling, on a camp-out or in the city as it pours from above, the AQUAMAX® 10.10 membrane will keep you dry while its breathability regulates your body climate. Taped seams and waterproof zippers eliminate the last possible weak spots and the storm hood protects your head and neck.    

\

Features:  AQUAMAX® 10.10 membrane, pre-formed elbows, storm hood, bottom adjustment, waterproof zippers, chin guard

For high-impact activities in hot climates that require long pants in spite of the weather, the extremely lightweight Broxton outdoor pants are truly making a difference. The technically looking light fabric is very stretchable and features both the moisture wicking and quick-drying DRY PLUS moisture technology and Polygiene®, which safely inhibits the growth of odour-causing bacteria and fungi. No matter what’s your activity and how hot it is, the Broxton pants will provide a maximum of body temperature management and won’t inhibit your freedom of movement, even when you are climbing or running fast. Two open front pockets, one zipped safety front pocket, and two zipped back pockets offer plenty of space for small items.

\

Technology: DRY PLUS moisture, Stretch, Polygiene®, YKK zippers

column13: Braxton Bermuda wms, McKinley, Mountain tec

column2:
The women’s Broxton Bermuda is a lightweight short pant for all mountain and outdoor sports. The light and stretchable fabric has a very technical look and features the DRY PLUS moisture technology, which guarantees reliable moisture transport and maximum comfort. \

column13: Ewa Softshell Jacket ux, Mountain tec, McKinley

column2:
When the conditions get really cold and wet, the Ewa jacket is the one piece of equipment you definitely want to bring along. Nothing beats the price/performance ratio of this comfortable and highly protective three-layer softshell. column13: Lanila Padded Jacket wms, Mountain tec, McKinley

column2:
If you need extra warmth on your trekking expedition or hiking trip without a bulky feel and excessive weight, the women’s Lanila padded jacket with PrimaLoft® insulation is not only one of the most functional jackets you can bring, but probably one of the best looking, too. The Lanila can be worn as an insulating mid layer or as an outer layer. A durable water repellent finish makes sure that you don’t get soaked. Besides, the PrimaLoft® fibres are enclosed by a wind-breaking, high-density Polyamid fabric that blocks the wind to keep you warm. The entire jacket, including a storm hood, packs into an internal pocket, so you can bring it along anywhere, anytime.

The Polar jacket is a second layer fleece that can be used\
in three different ways: as a regular second layer; as a\
stand-alone fleece; or with outerwear marked „M.Z.S.“\
(McKinley Zip-In System). The Polar can be zipped to\
the latter to create a single, insulating, cold-weather\
jacket for more challenging conditions. The high-quality\
Polartec® fleece jacket is guaranteed to keep you\
warm and comfortable. Available in both women’s and\
men’s styles, cuts and sizes.\
\
Material: 100% Polyester\
\
Features: pre-formed elbows, bottom adjustment,\
chin guard\
\
Technology: Polartec®, M.Z.S. (McKinley Zip-In System)\

column13: Ales wms shell, McKinley, Active Outdoor

column3: Real Outdoor enthusiasts need reliable all-condition\
garments like the functional Ales hardshell jacket for\
women. The AQUAMAX® 2-layer laminate with taped\
seams is comfortable to wear during physical activities\
in wind, rain and snow. The membrane is windproof,\
waterproof and breathable. Extra protection to keep\
wind and weather out is offered by the taped seams, the\
detachable storm hood and a bottom adjustment. Great\
fit for hikers and trekkers!\
\
Material: 100% Polyester\
\
Performance: 2-layer laminate\
\
Water column: 5,000 mm\
\
Breathability: 5,000 g/m2/24h\
\
Features: taped seams, pre-formed elbows,\
AQUAMAX® laminate, snap-off/packable storm hood,\
bottom adjustment\
\
Technology: AQUAMAX® 5.5\

column13: Coddy men, Mc Kinley, Active Outdoor

column3: The Coddy pants are our top functional Active Outdoor\
trekking pants, equipped with DRY PLUS and UV protection.\
With its many useful features, it is an essential\
part of your equipment: DRY PLUS and Polygiene® take\
care of your microclimate and keep you dry and free of\
odour-causing bacteria and fungi; with the bottom leg\
zippers, you can comfortably wear light low-cut outdoor\
shoes as well as hiking boots; the pre-formed knees, the\
partially elastic waist and the integrated belt ensure\
perfect fit. Last but not least: The zip-off function converts\
the Coddy into functional outdoor shorts for hot\
summer days. Great garment for travelling. Also available\
in special sizes for longer or shorter legs.\
\
Material: 100% Nylon\
\
Features: pre-formed knees, partial elastic waist,\
bottom-zip opening, integrated belt, zip-off pants\
\
Technology: DRY PLUS moisture, sun protection UPF 50,\
Polygiene®\

column3: These very functional outdoor zip-off pants are equipped\

body and to inhibit any odour-causing bacteria or\
fungi. This regulates your microclimate and keeps you\
dry and cool at any time. The pre-formed knees, the\
stretch fabric and the integrated belt of these pants\
ensure perfect fit. The zip-off function converts the\
Mendoran into functional outdoor shorts for hot summer\
days. Perfect also for travelling. Also available in\
special sizes for longer or shorter legs.\
\

\

column13: Emerson Hard Shell Rain Jacket ux

column2:
Lightweight and reliable hard shell for rainy days. Whether you wear your Emerson jacket in the mountains, travelling, on a camp-out or in the city as it pours from above, the AQUAMAX® 10.10 membrane will keep you dry while its breathability regulates your body climate. Taped seams and waterproof zippers eliminate the last possible weak spots and the storm hood protects your head and neck.    

\

Features:  AQUAMAX® 10.10 membrane, pre-formed elbows, storm hood, bottom adjustment, waterproof zippers, chin guard
\

column13: Trekker CL, Footwear, McKinley, Mountain Tec

column3: McKINLEY’s Trekker CL is a classic full-leather trekking\
and hiking boot designed for real outdoor adventures.\
The lasted construction with leather lining and\
collar guarantees ultimate comfort and an unbeatable\
feeling inside the boot. The stability and durability\
needed for extended, technical trekking is provided by\
the high-quality leather upper and the robust, traditional\
lacing system with metal hooks and a deep pull\
hook at the ankles. A rubber toe cup and a heel cup\
protect the foot against impact and offer additional\
stability.\
Material: Full Leather, oiled\
Liner: Leather\
Outsole: Vibram® (STICO 3)\
Midsole: PU\
Construction: Lasted\
Weight: 860 g\
Special: Comfort Fit, Deep Pull Hook, Metal Hook,\
Heel Protector, Rubber Toe Protector\

column13: Cisco Comfort W, McKinley, Active Outdoor

column3: Very well equipped multi-functional shoe for a variety\
of outdoor activities, travel or everyday use. This version\
of McKINLEY’s Cisco was designed to deliver the\
utmost comfort possible for long and strenuous days out\
on the road or in the mountains. This was the challenge\
that the McKinley footwear designers had to face, and\
they came up with lightweight and durable materials,\
Ortholite insoles (one of the leading insoles for comfort\
and fit) and a Contragrip® outsole featuring a unique\
combination of a special rubber compound, tread geometry,\
and density for effortless walking or hiking with\
optimal grip. The liner of this boot is equipped with\
McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX® technology.\
Material: Suede Leather/Synthetic & Mesh\
Liner: Synthetic\
Outsole: McKINLEY Hiking Contragrip Rubber (STICO 2)\
Midsole: molded EVA (high cut)\
Weight: 415 g\
Special: AQUAMAX®, Ortholite®, Performance Fit,\
Metal Hook, Easy Entry Loop, Heel Protector,\
Rubber Toe Protector, Comfort Cushion System\

column13: Sequence AQX M, McKinely, Active Outdoor

column3: The Sequence AQX is a waterproof, well cushioned, and lightweight\
outdoor boot designed to offer maximum performance,\
comfort, and breathability. Although it is made of the lightest\
materials available, it offers enough support for serious trekking\
and hiking. The anatomical shape of the collar enhances the freedom\
of movement while supporting and protecting the Achilles\
area. The overall construction of the boot is based on McKINLEY’s\
new Butterfly footwear technology, featuring the new Butterfly\
Shank and the Butterfly Lacing Support. The Butterfly Shank is a\
thermoplastic urethane link in the outsole between the heel and\
the forefoot that allows a smooth and stable impact when the foot\
hits the ground. It also provides torsional stability and strength\
to the midfoot, thus supporting an easy toe-off. The new Butterfly\
Lacing Support is a „wrap-around“ lacing design that links the\
classic metal-hook lacing to the boot’s upper for a more individual\
adjustment. In addition to the Butterfly Technology features, the\
Sequence AQX is equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX\
® technology, making this extremely versatile lightweight\
boot super reliable in all conditions.\
Material: Synthetic & Mesh\
Liner: Synthetic\
Outsole: Rubber (STICO 3)\
Midsole: molded EVA (high cut)\
Weight: 530 g\
Special: AQUAMAX®, Ortholite®, Performance Fit, Butterf ly\
Shank, Butterf ly Lacing Support, Deep Pull Hook, Metal\
Hook, Rubber Toe Protector, Comfort Cushion System\

column13: Magma AQX M, Mountain Tec, McKinley

column3: The Magma AQX is one of McKINLEY’s Active Outdoor trekking\
and hiking boots that is designed for maximum performance\
with minimum weight. It’s a great choice for outdoor\
enthusiasts looking for a versatile trekking boot at a highly\
competitive price. With an upper made of leather and synthetic,\
the Magma AQX is also equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof\
AQUAMAX® technology, making this all-rounder reliable\
in all conditions. In addition, the VIBRAM® outsole\
provides tremendous grip in any kind of weather and terrain.\
Its durable compound ensures extended life and extremely\
high friction on all surfaces. For ideal fit, the Magma AQX\
features a classic lacing system that runs through durable\
metal hooks with an additional deep pull hook and Butterfly\
support that links the lacing directly to the upper for a more\
individual adjustment.\
Material: Leather/Synthetic / Textile\
Liner: Synthetic\
Outsole: Vibram® (STICO 2)\
Midsole: PU\
Weight: 590 g\
Special: AQUAMAX®, Comfort Fit, Butterf ly Lacing\
Support, Deep Pull Hook, Metal Hook, Heel Protector,\
Rubber Toe Protector\

column13: Sequence AQX W, McKinely, Active Outdoor

column3: The Sequence AQX is a waterproof, well cushioned, and lightweight\
outdoor boot designed to offer maximum performance,\
comfort, and breathability. Although it is made of the lightest\
materials available, it offers enough support for serious trekking\
and hiking. The anatomical shape of the collar enhances the freedom\
of movement while supporting and protecting the Achilles\
area. The overall construction of the boot is based on McKINLEY’s\
new Butterfly footwear technology, featuring the new Butterfly\
Shank and the Butterfly Lacing Support. The Butterfly Shank is a\
thermoplastic urethane link in the outsole between the heel and\
the forefoot that allows a smooth and stable impact when the foot\
hits the ground. It also provides torsional stability and strength\
to the midfoot, thus supporting an easy toe-off. The new Butterfly\
Lacing Support is a „wrap-around“ lacing design that links the\
classic metal-hook lacing to the boot’s upper for a more individual\
adjustment. In addition to the Butterfly Technology features, the\
Sequence AQX is equipped with McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX\
® technology, making this extremely versatile lightweight\
boot super reliable in all conditions.\
Material: Synthetic & Mesh\
Liner: Synthetic\
Outsole: Rubber (STICO 3)\
Midsole: molded EVA (high cut)\
Weight: 450 g\
Special: AQUAMAX®, Ortholite®, Performance Fit, Butterf ly\
Shank, Butterf ly Lacing Support, Deep Pull Hook, Metal\
Hook, Rubber Toe Protector, Comfort Cushion System\

column13: Trekker CL, Footwear, McKinley, Mountain Tec

column3: McKINLEY’s Trekker CL is a classic full-leather trekking\
and hiking boot designed for real outdoor adventures.\
The lasted construction with leather lining and\
collar guarantees ultimate comfort and an unbeatable\
feeling inside the boot. The stability and durability\
needed for extended, technical trekking is provided by\
the high-quality leather upper and the robust, traditional\
lacing system with metal hooks and a deep pull\
hook at the ankles. A rubber toe cup and a heel cup\
protect the foot against impact and offer additional\
stability.\
Material: Full Leather, oiled\
Liner: Leather\
Outsole: Vibram® (STICO 3)\
Midsole: PU\
Construction: Lasted\
Weight: 860 g\
Special: Comfort Fit, Deep Pull Hook, Metal Hook,\
Heel Protector, Rubber Toe Protector\

column13: Cisco Comfort W, McKinley, Active Outdoor

column3: Very well equipped multi-functional shoe for a variety\
of outdoor activities, travel or everyday use. This version\
of McKINLEY’s Cisco was designed to deliver the\
utmost comfort possible for long and strenuous days out\
on the road or in the mountains. This was the challenge\
that the McKinley footwear designers had to face, and\
they came up with lightweight and durable materials,\
Ortholite insoles (one of the leading insoles for comfort\
and fit) and a Contragrip® outsole featuring a unique\
combination of a special rubber compound, tread geometry,\
and density for effortless walking or hiking with\
optimal grip. The liner of this boot is equipped with\
McKINLEY’s waterproof AQUAMAX® technology.\
Material: Suede Leather/Synthetic & Mesh\
Liner: Synthetic\
Outsole: McKINLEY Hiking Contragrip Rubber (STICO 2)\
Midsole: molded EVA (high cut)\
Weight: 415 g\
Special: AQUAMAX®, Ortholite®, Performance Fit,\
Metal Hook, Easy Entry Loop, Heel Protector,\
Rubber Toe Protector, Comfort Cushion System\
The Helix is McKINLEY’s ultra comfortable walking\
shoe for everyday use, which is inspired by the rugged\
challenges of the Great Outdoors. The breathable and\
smooth suede leather upper of the Helix guarantees a\
balanced foot climate and a comfortable feeling inside\
the shoe. The outsole features McKINLEY’s new Butterf\
ly Grip Zone, which delivers a high level of grip even\
on uneven or rougher surfaces. The Gilly lacing system\
ensures a comfortable and snug fit. Whether you are\
travelling, hiking, or just walking around town, the\
Helix is a great and comfortable choice.\
Material: Full Suede Leather & Mesh\
Liner: Synthetic\
Outsole: Rubber\
Midsole: molded EVA (low cut)\
Special: Butterf ly Grip Zone, Gilly Lacing,\
Rubber Toe Protector\

The Chromosome is a very athletic, well-cushioned and\
highly breathable trail shoe for ambitious speed hikers,\
trail runners but it´s also great for everyday use. The\
construction of the shoe is based on McKINLEY’s new\
BUTTERFLY footwear technology. Being part of the\
X-Function collection, the lightest materials were used\
to offer the best functionality for active outdoor athletes.\
The lightweight upper of the Chromosome offers\
maximum performance and air permeability. The special\
Butterfly Lacing Support allows you to individually\
adjust the fit by applying different pressure and tightness\
in different strategic areas around the foot. The\
outsole features the new Butterfly grip zone, which\
delivers reliable grip even in uneven or rougher terrain.\
The Chromosome is designed to perform!\
